org.openhab.binding.velux.internal

Enum VeluxItemType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<VeluxItemType>
      • org.openhab.binding.velux.internal.VeluxItemType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<VeluxItemType>

    @NonNullByDefault
public enum VeluxItemType
extends java.lang.Enum<VeluxItemType>
    Enumeration of Types of a Velux item.
    Provides information about:
    • associated thing identified by String
    • defined channel identified by String
    • getItemClass() item class,
    • isReadable() about a read possibility,
    • isWritable() about a write possibility,
    • isExecutable() about an execute possibility,
    • isToBeRefreshed() about necessarily to be refreshed,
    • isToBeRefreshedNow(int, org.eclipse.smarthome.core.thing.ThingTypeUID, java.lang.String) about necessarily to be refreshed at this time,
    • isChannel() as indication of being handled as Channel of a thing,
    • isProperty() as indication of being handled as property of a thing.
    In addition there are helper methods providing information about:
    • getIdentifier() returning the common identifier string,
    • getByThingAndChannel(org.eclipse.smarthome.core.thing.ThingTypeUID, java.lang.String) to retrieve an enum instance selected by Thing and Channel identifier,
    • getPropertyEntriesByThing(org.eclipse.smarthome.core.thing.ThingTypeUID) to retrieve any Thing identifiers as array of String,

    Within this enumeration, the expected behaviour of the OpenHAB item (resp. Channel or Property) is set. For each kind of Channel (i.e. bridge or device) parameter a set of information is defined:

    • Unique identification by:
      • Thing name as string,
      • Channel name as string,
    • Channel type as OpenHAB type,
    • ability flag whether this item is to be read,
    • ability flag whether this item is able to be modified,
    • ability flag whether this item is to be used as execution trigger.
    Author:
    Guenther Schreiner - Initial contribution
